  <body>
    <section name="Introduction">
      <subsection name="What is Hippo Utilities forge project">
        <p> The Hippo Utilities forge project contains generic code for reusage, in order to avoid code being copied from project to project. </p>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="Code base on GitHub">
        <p>The code is on GitHub at <a href="https://github.com/bloomreach-forge/hippo-utilities/">https://github.com/bloomreach-forge/hippo-utilities/</a>.</p>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="Feature overview">
        <p>There are four artifacts available, targeted for CMS, repository and HST, plus one common artifact.</p>

        <b>hippo-utilities-commons</b>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="commons/annotationutil.html">Annotation Utility</a></li>
          <li><a href="commons/genericsutil.html">Generics Utility</a></li>
          <li><a href="commons/hippoutil.html">Hippo Utility</a></li>
          <li><a href="commons/repositoryutil.html">Repository Utility</a></li>
          <li><a href="commons/ftpclient.html">Simple FTP Client</a></li>
          <li><a href="commons/jcrmockup.html">JCR Mockup to create a node structure based on system view XML</a></li>
        </ul>

        <b>hippo-utilities-hst</b>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="hst/computil.html">Component utility methods (e.g. get parameter with a default)</a></li>
          <li><a href="hst/components.html">Base components</a> reading id and class config for div, also Container component
            reading HST subcomponents dynamically, RedirectComponent and ForwardComponent</li>
          <li><a href="hst/cookie.html">Cookie support check utility</a></li>
          <li><a href="hst/paging.html">Paging</a></li>
          <li><a href="hst/xmlstripper.html">XML Stripper</a></li>
          <li>Annotation based reading of repository nodes, for example for configuration nodes outside of
            /content/documents</li>
        </ul>

        <b>hippo-utilities-repository</b>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="repository/updater-exec-sched-job.html">Groovy Updater Execution Scheduler Job</a></li>
        </ul>

      </subsection>

    </section>
  </body>
</document>
